lyrics:
3 contributorsmust get out demo lyricsverse 1
ive been the needle and the thread
weaving figure eights and circles round your head
i try to laugh but cry instead
stretch my hands and feet to the corner of your bed

prechorus
fumbling through your dresser drawer
forgot what i was looking for
try to guide me in the right direction
making use of all this time
keeping everything inside
close my eyes and listen to you cry

chorus

im letting you down
im dancing til dawn
im fooling around
im not giving up
im making your love
this citys made us crazy and we must get out

down these jagged streets and into my bed
